cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on information dissemination protocols for ad-hoc wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses a generalized model of interference, which could potentially fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper presents randomized and deterministic protocols, which could fall under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper utilizes simulations to compare the performance of their protocol against previous work, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
